 into the story, making sure not to start your own independent one.  <br>
   Making a quick origin is fine, but hopefull you understand what we're going for.  For help, please look at the RPG by NeoAngel and Bythegun.  So, without further ado... here we go!<br>
  (One more thing... please leave sort of a hook at the end of your story so that we can take off from where you left off.)<br>
<br>
<br>
   Sid look out the window of his two story apartment.  Outside he saw Mrs. Murphey and her two kids piling out of their old Jalopy of a car and hustle into their city-sponsered living domicile.  He heard the heavy metal cords of a radio playing five blocks away.  As far as the eye could see the common people of the city, or so affectionatly called 'rats' were out and about.  Doing what they could to survive.  <br>
   Just down the street three gang leaders, or 'wolves' were beating down a common man.  No matter what you did, in this neighborhood, you just couldn't get away from wolves.  <br>
   Course wolves were just answering to their superiors, lions, and lions to the top section, sharks.<br>
   Slowly twirling around the cigerette in his hand, Sid took a drag and puffed it out slow, thinking about moving to a nicer part of the city.  A place where wolves, lions, and sharks just weren't heard of.  Shaking his head, he quickly dismissed the thought.  He couldn't live anywhere else but here.  He was too old, too tough.  Besides, no matter where you go, you can't get away from a wolf or two...<br>
   Just then, a classy dame walked into the dark office.  The ceiling fan just barely making up for the extreme heat, she was wearing a long silky outfit.  The sorta outfit with class.  Sid looked up.  Buisness?<br>
    She started the conversation.  &quot;I gotta problem.  I heard you could help.&quot; Her voice sensual and full of flavor.<br>
   Gruffly he replied, &quot;Yeah, well honey we all got problems.  Some of 'em you can fix, and some of 'em y'cant.  For example, I got this rash just below my belt an-&quot;<br>
   &quot;This is one you can fix.&quot;<br>
   &quot;We'll see.&quot;<br>
   She paced the room slowly.  &quot;There's a bounty on my head.  50 million credits.&quot;<br>
   He sneered. &quot;So what makes you think that I aint gonna turn you in and make a tidy profit.&quot;<br>
   &quot;Because I have 100 million.&quot;<br>
   At this he sat back.  &quot;100 mil?  Let's talk beautiful...&quot;<br>
   &quot;You find who did this.  You find who's behind my bounty.  I've never done anything really bad in my whole life, and-&quot; By this time she was crying &quot;-and I don't want to die.&quot;<br>
   &quot;I'll need my money upfront.&quot;<br>
   &quot;I have my identity card right here.&quot;<br>
   &quot;Fine.  I'll make sure you have it, withdraw when I'm through.  And if you cheat me lady, if you cheat me?  Well let's just say I ain't never hit a lady, but shoot'em?  That's a whole different story...&quot;<br>
   &quot;I see.  I'm going to be in a safe place for awhile.  Ten days.  You have that much time to find him.&quot;<br>
   &quot;I do huh?  Well I better get to work.  Get out my office.  And don't let the door hit your-&quot;<br>
   With that she left at a quick pace.  She left behind her bank card with a lipstick kiss on it.  &quot;Signed Roxy&quot;  Sid sighed.  Gonna be a long night.  But he knew just who to talk to... someone with all the answers... with that he walked downstairs and out the street to ____________'s house.  <br>
<br>
