<br>
Leo was the type of person you never turned your back on, and never looked directly in the eye for too long of a time. His blood shot gaze could scare away any rat in the city with but a look, only the sharks who gave him orders would make eye contact. Not even his wolves would dare to do that. Sid didn't like dealing with the maniac, but buisness was buisness, work was work, and both of those had been hard to come by lately. A rat could get a lion out of a net trap, and Leo owed him a favor. <br>
<br>
Knocking on Leo's door with his knuckle, Sid took a final drag off his ciggy and flung it away. A panel slid open revealing those dark eyes, and darker hair all but covering one of them. Leo's voice was as gruff as his appearance. <br>
<br>
&quot;Whadya want?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;A favor.&quot;<br>
<br>
The eyes blinked, apparently recognizing him. &quot;Oh,&quot; said Leo,  and the heavy iron door creaked open. <br>
<br>
Leo's office was twice as messy as his own, and with Sid's disaster of an appartment, that was saying alot. Before the door slammed shut behind him with a resounding bang, Leo was already in his seat with his unshaven chin on his hands and his elbows on his desk. Tossing &quot;Roxy's&quot; card onto the table Sid said, &quot;Check her out for me.&quot;<br>
<br>
Leo held the card under the light and considered it for a moment, then said, &quot;Ok, gimme a couple of days.&quot; With that said, Leo promptly ignored Sid until he let himself out. <br>
<br>
Sid had no intention of letting those two days go to waste. 100 million creds was alot of cigerettes. He had posed as a bounty hunter before, and he could do it again. He knew where they hung out, and so he made his way to _________. <p>&quot;Death is lighter than a feather, duty, heavier than a mountain.&quot;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mrbeaver@polykarbonbbs>MrBeaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/15/02 10:48:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=857.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Continuing...</span><hr size=1> He knew where they hung out, and so he made his way to the local bar down the the street a ways.  The Hole.  <br>
   The Hole was the type of place that people didn't go to unless they had a mean bit of buisness to attend to.  Sid had plenty of this on his plate, and he pushed the door open and walked in.<br>
   Smoke hung like fog and the stench of Rats and Wolves lingered in the air.  Noting to himself that it had gotten a bit cleaner since he got here, he brushed off the stool and sat down.<br>
   &quot;Whadda ya want?  Shnaps, Vodka?&quot; Asked the bartender.  A big burly man.  &quot;Course it'll cost ya quite a bit.  Alcohol's scarce in this part of Grunge-City.  Especially good alcohol...&quot;<br>
   Trying not to look to obvious, Sid lit up a cigarette.  &quot;I need information on a job goin' down.&quot;<br>
   The bartender's gaze wasn't directed at Sid, but his voice was.  &quot;What job?&quot;<br>
   &quot;A dame's being hunted down.&quot;<br>
   &quot;I don't blame 'em.&quot;<br>
   &quot;So you know about it.&quot;<br>
   &quot;Course I do.&quot; The bartender said igdignitly. &quot;Just about every bounty hunter's been hanging around lately.&quot;  He pointed to the far corner, where three men sat on the sticky vinal bench.  &quot;Those three?  They just came in today.  50 million will do that to you.&quot;<br>
   &quot;Y'know why they want her?&quot;<br>
   &quot;This chick?  Na, I know that people are after her, but I don't know who.  Word is...&quot;<br>
   &quot;What?&quot;<br>
   &quot;Well I can't remember.  Maybe if I had a little grease to help the wheels turh a bit smoother...&quot;<br>
   Sid handed him 200 credits.  &quot;'ere you go.  Now talk.&quot;<br>
   &quot;OK, I'll tell you.....&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theunknownwriter>TheUnknownWriter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fresh Meat</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/15/02 4:43:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=857.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> This is kinda a cool story</span><hr size=1> I'll join.<br>
