The bartender continued. &quot;See, but the only problem is... I can't let anyone know about this little, 'conversation' between us.  Lot of bad buisness see?  So this is where we say goodbye.&quot;  The bartender slowly pulled out a handgun from under the bar.  Sid saw this and took the cig from his mouth and shoved it into the bartender's eye.  He screamed.  Opening his other eye, the bartender tried to aim the gun.  Sid lept over the bar and picked up a bottle of wine.  In one continous movement he smashed the side of the bottle into the bartender's face.<br>
